President
Cyril Ramaphosa is expected to assess Mpumalanga's provincial response to the
Covid-19 pandemic. The visit
follows oversight visits by the President to Gauteng, KwaZulu-Natal, Eastern
Cape and Western Cape to evaluate the fight against Covid-19. According
to the president's spokeswoman, Khusela Diko, Ramaphosa will commence his visit
by receiving a presentation from the Provincial Command Council on the
provinceâ€™s Covid-19 response strategy. "He
will then proceed to the Cyril Clarke Secondary School to monitor progress made
in managing the impact and spread of the virus in schools." She said
the visit will culminate in a visit to the Rob Ferreira Hospital as a
designated hospital for managing the Covid-19 cases. Ramaphosa
will be accompanied by Minister of Health, Dr Zweli Mkhize; Minister in the
Presidency, Jackson Mthembu; Minister of Basic Education, Angie Motshekga and
Mpumalanga Premier, Refilwe Mtshweni-Tsipane on his inspection of Covid-19
facilities. Mpumalanga
has so far recorded 1478 cases with 4 deaths and 520 recoveries.